snippet.title: New Security Measures at the Eiffel Tower and Good News Coffee
snippet.description:
The new security wall at the Eiffel Tower is almost finished, which will be really nice because it's been a hideous construction mess for forever. Also a quick trip to Good News Coffee! Motherboard Cali Guys Podcast: http://bit.ly/MotherboardPod Help me make better videos at http://patreon.com/jayswanson and then find me on the internet in all of the usual spots:

Grab my guide to Paris here: http://bit.ly/ParisVloggersGuide

More swag here:
http://bit.ly/ShirtOfTheMonth (shirts and hat)
http://bit.ly/JaysGearList (my gear and books)
https://gum.co/camerafour (Disposable Camera Four digital scans)

Follow me here:
http://twitter.com/jayonaboat
http://instagram.com/jayswanson

Music by: Dyalla

My name is Jay Swanson - I'm an American writer living in Paris on an artist visa and hoping to make the city of light my home base - at least for the foreseeable future. I write science-fiction and fantasy, vlog daily, and love pizza a little too much.

Links below to Amazon are affiliate links - meaning if you click through them and buy something, I'll get some pennies. Thanks! (The FTC wants me to tell you that up front)

FAQ:
How long have you lived in France? On and off for over two years.

What do you miss most about ho- NACHOS

You're always talking about living on some ship. WHAT SHIP? - I made a "Draw My Life" video that explains a lot here: https://youtu.be/-MrvL37jTKM

Where are you from originally? - Pullman, Washington - a small university/agricultural town near Idaho (and yes, the potatoes are amazing).

What do you film with? - I've made a lot of changes recently, but I try to keep my gear list up to date if you want to see what I use and buy some for yourself: http://bit.ly/JaysGearList

What do you edit with? - Adobe Premiere - it's pretty much all I've ever used since high school.

Aren't you ever freaked out by leaving your camera behind to film yourself? - Yep. But not too badly - I tend to be careful when I do.

Why are you living in #Paris? - Because I've always wanted to; I feel at home here: https://youtu.be/4Vivf6MqMxQ

Do you speak French? Oui. https://youtu.be/va1QjaHgij8

You talk a lot about the books you're working on, what are they about? - They're sci-fi (and fantasy) and I've got a decent pitch for you here: https://youtu.be/W2bKt4_Tp4E

Do you make money off YouTube? - Ha, no. I wish. It took me over 500 videos to make my first total $100 off adsense. I think it will slowly change, but VERY slowly.

I really enjoy your videos, how can I support you? - The easiest and best way to support me is through Patreon, where you can pitch in as little as $1/mo to help me make better videos: http://patreon.com/jayswanson

I don't trust this Patreon thing - can I just paypal you? - Here's my ko-fi if that's your thing (and coffee is your game): https://ko-fi.com/jayswanson

But I want to send you something tangible! - I do have a wishlist on Amazon, though it's a bit complicated with the international shipping situation. This is the US one: http://amzn.to/2ykS9Ux

And here's the French wishlist: http://bit.ly/JaysFrenchWishList

Thanks for watching!

comments.textDisplay: Question  from my wife ... Why do thy serve Coffee in a glass and not a Cup  or Mug  her  thinking is it  would be to hot to hold
comments.textOriginal: Question  from my wife ... Why do thy serve Coffee in a glass and not a Cup  or Mug  her  thinking is it  would be to hot to hold

replies.textDisplay: It's not so bad - probably for the aesthetic first, and the cooling second. A good cup of coffee changes flavors as it cools, so you don't want it to stay hot for too long if the plan is to sit and enjoy it. There might be other reasons but that would be my first guess (I prefer mugs too but I'll take whatever I can get 😂)

replies.textDisplay:
Great question that's regularly on my mind. Largely because finding music is a lengthy and energy-consuming process. You have to find music that

A) fits your style
B) isn't copyright protected
C) is affordable
D) comes in a quantity that doesn't require you to recycle it too quickly (when you upload every day like I do).

There's a lot of music out there that fits some of these categories, very few that fit all of them, and in the end is a daunting task. It takes a lot of time to dig through music libraries and individual artists. All that said, I do want to switch it up and it's been on my list of things to do for forever, but every attempt has ended pretty quickly in frustration. It would have been at the top of my list of things to do on a break between seasons, but I didn't wind up taking one. I think I just found someone new I can work with this week, so hopefully that helps to mix things up, and I'll keep looking! 😀

comments.textDisplay: I am super psyched your WASHER is HOOKED UP!  I will enjoy seeing how you end up drying things :)  Do you take your coffee sans sugar/cream?  All the years we lived in Germany one of the best things was how fresh and real the food was.  When you bought lunch or items to bring home it was made a few hours before, nothing processed/frozen from a company that made thousands of pies an hour...  That's another rant for another day, I miss the fresh healthy food.  I love watching you zoom around on the wheel, you maneuver so well, a real pro now!  It looks effortless, seeing you swirl in and around, it's exhilarating!  Lovely area around the Eiffel tower, and I learned a new French word (!) "Interdit"  (forbidden) i.e. verboten!  Hope you and everyone has a great weekend!
